content.question:
Consider the following code segment.

int count = 0;
for (int k = 0; k < 10; k++)
{
count++;
}
System.out.println(count);
Which of the following code segments will produce the same output as the code segment above?

choices.label:
int count = 0;
for (int k = 1; k < 10; k++)
{
count++;
}
System.out.println(count);

int count = 1;
for (int k = 1; k <= 10; k++)
{
count++;
}
System.out.println(count);

int count = 1;
for (int k = 0; k <= 9; k++)
{
count++;
}
System.out.println(count);

int count = 0;
for (int k = 9; k >= 0; k--)
{
count++;
}
System.out.println(count);

content.answer:
int count = 0;
for (int k = 9; k >= 0; k--)
{
count++;
}
System.out.println(count);
